" Coles and Woolworths consider [that] if the shelves are full, if products such as toilet paper rolls and disinfectants can be [purchased] and are available in large quantities, this will likely reduce panic," said Russell Zimmerman to ABC News.
The manufacturer of recycled toilet paper Who Gives has Crap said last Wednesday that they were out of stock.
Kimberly-Clark, who manufactures Kleenex toilet paper, and Solaris Paper, who manufactures Sorbent paper, noted that they are working 24/7 to maintain supply, according to News.com.au's article.
Domain.com, a real estate site, indicated that some real estate sellers offered free toilet paper to the first bidder at auctions in Melbourne, while fewer auctions were organized because buyers were on leave during the long weekend of Labour Day.
The Thursday edition of NT News, a Darwin-printed daily, included an eight-page insert to be cut and used as toilet paper.
