On Wednesday, the World Health Organization (WHO) called the current epidemic VOCID-19 (the disease caused by the SARS-CoV-2 coronavirus) a pandemic.
Although the word "pandemic" refers only to the degree of spread of the disease, not to the dangerousness of specific cases, WHO has indicated the need to push governments to action:
"All countries can still change the course of this pandemic.
If countries detect, test, treat, isolate, locate and mobilize their populations as part of the response," said Tedros Adhanom Ghebreyesus, WHO Director General.
